<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Rumania/148a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Rumania (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to">Wilson</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 248</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-28">June 28,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of
                                intergovernmental debts and transmits for the information of the
                                American Minister copy of the “Agreement between the Kingdom of
                                Rumania and the United States of America, June 11, 1932”.<note n="64" xml:id="d441fn64">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, pp. 305–306.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>